    "summary": [
      "Ten years after the Paris Agreement, signed in Le Bourget, France on December 12, 2015, global average temperatures in 2024 reached 1.45°C above the 1850-1900 baseline, according to the IPCC's Sixth Assessment Report.",
      "In 2023, global CO₂ emissions hit a record 37.4 gigaton, as reported by the Global Carbon Project, while the European Union, led by former President Ursula von der Leyen, reduced emissions by 32% since 1990.",
      "The COP30 summit, planned for November 2025 in Belém, Brazil, will be a crucial test for international commitment, with UN Secretary-General António Guterres urging countries to submit updated Nationally Determined Contributions (NDCs) with more ambitious goals for 2035."
    ],
